VL  - 19
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper shows that the widely appearing ?marginal cost? formulations of the dynamic, periodic review, stochastic cash balance problem are equivalent to a ?total cost? formulation, as long as the holding, shortage cost, and ?closing of account? functions are constructed correctly.
AB  - This paper shows that the widely appearing ?marginal cost? formulations of the dynamic, periodic review, stochastic cash balance problem are equivalent to a ?total cost? formulation, as long as the holding, shortage cost, and ?closing of account? functions are constructed correctly.
