T1  - Mathematical Programming Methods of Pattern Classification
AU  - Grinold, Richard C.
Y1  - 1972/11/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.19.3.272
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.19.3.272
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 272
EP  - 289
VL  - 19
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This survey examines eight mathematical programming models of pattern classification. The paper determines the range of applicability and computational merits of each model. The flexibility and large sample properties of the models are also discussed. We find that six of the models produce decision rules that maximize a function we call the quality of a decision rule. The remaining two models minimize a weighted sum of errors.
AB  - This survey examines eight mathematical programming models of pattern classification. The paper determines the range of applicability and computational merits of each model. The flexibility and large sample properties of the models are also discussed. We find that six of the models produce decision rules that maximize a function we call the quality of a decision rule. The remaining two models minimize a weighted sum of errors.
